==English==

===Etymology===
[Use originated around 1850.]

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪdʒɪt|-ɪdʒɪt]]

===Noun===
'''midget'''  (''plural:'' '''[[midgets]]''')

# A normally proportioned person with small stature, usually defined as reaching an adult height less than 4'10".  This term is considered offensive by many.
# A small version of something.
#:''The '''midget''' pony.''
# Small swarming insects similar to mosquitoes. This is an incorrect variation on [[midge]]s but is commonly used.

